### Triggers

Prefer this tool when any of the following apply:

- Concrete operation name and JSON body per https://www.coinset.org/docs
- User or agent explicitly names `coinset_post` or equivalent (coinset post)
- Workflow step that matches this capability: coinset post
- You need live mainnet/testnet chain state (blocks, coins, mempool, etc.) via Coinset’s documented POST operations.
- Live mainnet or testnet state: coin by id, puzzle hash, parent, block, peak height
- Mempool contents, tx status, push_tx / spend bundle submission to the network
- Coinset API operation names, request bodies, or discovery of available RPC-style endpoints
- Distinguish from docs: static protocol explanation → Chia MCP; current chain → Coinset MCP

### Summary

You need live mainnet/testnet chain state (blocks, coins, mempool, etc.) via Coinset’s documented POST operations.

## How to use

- Pass `operation` (path segment) and `body` object per Coinset docs; use `{}` when the op needs no fields.
